                            <comment id="13658979" author="stack" created="Wed, 15 May 2013 23:06:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jeffreyz&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jeffreyz&quot;&gt;Jeffrey Zhong&lt;/a&gt; Can this be closed?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13659006" author="jeffreyz" created="Wed, 15 May 2013 23:25:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is still nice to have to make code more clean.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13737196" author="stack" created="Mon, 12 Aug 2013 18:38:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Moving out.  This improvement is not being worked on for 0.95/0.96 (though nice to have)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13956682" author="stack" created="Tue, 1 Apr 2014 15:57:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jeffreyz&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jeffreyz&quot;&gt;Jeffrey Zhong&lt;/a&gt; Is this nice-to-have or a requirement when we have distributed log replay enabled?  If table is disabling will we lose data w/o it?  Thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jeffreyz&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jeffreyz&quot;&gt;Jeffrey Zhong&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13956776" author="jeffreyz" created="Tue, 1 Apr 2014 17:11:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is nice to have thing. We won&apos;t loss data when recovering a disabling table because recovering logic automatically switch back to recovered edits files for regions of a disabling table. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Introducing the new state will complicate AM logic and still can&apos;t get rid of recovered edit implementations as it&apos;s also used in snapshot. Therefore, the benefits to have a new state isn&apos;t that much. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
